WEBVTT

00:03.742 --> 00:04.091
.

00:04.134 --> 00:06.876
[regal music]

00:06.919 --> 00:10.358
♪

00:10.401 --> 00:12.882
- This place is beautiful.
Look at that.

00:12.925 --> 00:15.624
- Mm. When I transition
from airplanes to cars,

00:15.667 --> 00:18.018
I can't look out of a window
for days.

00:18.061 --> 00:21.021
♪

00:21.064 --> 00:22.283
- Man, that's really
unfortunate,

00:22.326 --> 00:23.893
but I'm glad you made it.

00:23.936 --> 00:25.025
Everything good with your show?

00:25.068 --> 00:26.504
You told them you were
on a hiatus?

00:26.548 --> 00:28.463
- Yeah. "Chatterbox" will have
a guest host for a week,

00:28.506 --> 00:31.161
either Mario Lopez
or an AI influencer,

00:31.205 --> 00:33.250
while I get back
to hard journalism:

00:33.294 --> 00:35.296
an in-depth article
on Dwayne Johnson's

00:35.339 --> 00:37.298
goodwill ambassador trip
to Gjelgjiughm

00:37.341 --> 00:40.083
with a secret agenda
of getting Prime Minister Honig

00:40.127 --> 00:41.519
to agree on a trade deal.

00:41.563 --> 00:42.825
- I'd read that.

00:42.868 --> 00:44.261
But only that. I think
if it went any longer,

00:44.305 --> 00:46.002
I'd just skim it.

00:46.046 --> 00:48.091
- Hmm.

00:48.135 --> 00:49.310
[phone chimes]

00:49.353 --> 00:50.441
I knew I was dealing

00:50.485 --> 00:52.269
with a reluctant subject
for my piece,

00:52.313 --> 00:54.228
but his barbs were nothing new
to me.

00:54.271 --> 00:55.403
[phone chimes]

00:56.839 --> 00:58.884
[birds singing]

00:58.928 --> 01:01.148
[flowing orchestral music]

01:01.191 --> 01:02.627
[pinball machine jangling]

01:02.671 --> 01:03.889
[bell rings]

01:03.933 --> 01:06.196
♪

01:06.240 --> 01:07.545
- Welcome to Gjelgjiughm.

01:07.589 --> 01:11.680
- [laughing]
Oh, this is amazing.

01:11.723 --> 01:13.682
- The prime minister
is very excited

01:13.725 --> 01:15.379
to meet you, Mr. Johnson.

01:15.423 --> 01:17.381
And unexpected friend.

01:17.425 --> 01:19.383
- Oh, um, I'm Randall Park.

01:19.427 --> 01:22.125
I--I was in
"Ant-Man and the Wasp."

01:22.169 --> 01:23.431
- She's just finishing up
a call,

01:23.474 --> 01:24.780
but she thought it might be fun

01:24.823 --> 01:26.651
for you to wait
in the memorabilia room.

01:26.695 --> 01:28.479
My name's Reid
if you need anything.

01:28.523 --> 01:30.699
It's a pleasure to have you
at the Gjelgjiughm Estate.

01:30.742 --> 01:33.658
- Thank you, Reid.
- Yeah, thank you. [chuckles]

01:33.702 --> 01:35.399
Oh, my God, look at this.
- Look at this.

01:35.443 --> 01:36.966
[both laugh]
Wow.

01:37.009 --> 01:42.232
- If you smell...
- What the Randall is cookin'!

01:42.276 --> 01:44.321
[chuckling]
Oh, my God.

01:44.365 --> 01:46.497
"WrestleFest."

01:46.541 --> 01:48.499
I can't believe
she has this game.

01:48.543 --> 01:51.763
Oh, man.
This takes me way back.

01:51.807 --> 01:54.201
I remember the last time
I played this. [chuckles]

01:54.244 --> 01:55.985
[soft upbeat music]

01:56.028 --> 01:58.901
It was the summer after
I graduated high school.

01:58.944 --> 02:00.294
I was just a few weeks away

02:00.337 --> 02:02.383
from heading off to Miami
to play football.

02:02.426 --> 02:04.124
- Morning, Dewey.
How'd you sleep?

02:04.167 --> 02:05.473
- Terrible.
There was a drunk dude

02:05.516 --> 02:07.475
arguing with a trash can
outside my window.

02:07.518 --> 02:09.041
He kept banging on it
and yelling

02:09.085 --> 02:11.261
for Oscar the Grouch to pop out
and fight him like a man.

02:11.305 --> 02:12.958
- So detailed.

02:13.002 --> 02:16.179
Breakfast is ready.

02:16.223 --> 02:17.789
- What's this?
- This is a, uh--

02:17.833 --> 02:19.617
a hash brown
shaped like a stegosaurus.

02:19.661 --> 02:21.184
- How am I supposed to
bulk up for football

02:21.228 --> 02:23.795
with this very tiny,
very cute hashbrown?

02:23.839 --> 02:25.580
- Do some push-ups?

02:25.623 --> 02:27.582
I'm sorry.
It was on sale.

02:27.625 --> 02:30.062
We have to tighten our belts
this month.

02:30.106 --> 02:32.674
- I promise you, Mom,
when I make it to the NFL,

02:32.717 --> 02:34.458
we're never gonna have
to worry about money again.

02:34.502 --> 02:38.027
- I know, baby. Okay.
I gotta go to work.

02:38.070 --> 02:39.289
I have five houses to clean,

02:39.333 --> 02:40.334
and I'd like to make it
to my second house

02:40.377 --> 02:41.639
in time to catch the mailman.

02:41.683 --> 02:44.076
Turns out the post office
is dramatic,

02:44.120 --> 02:46.644
and he has all the best gossip.

02:46.688 --> 02:47.863
[smooches]

02:52.824 --> 02:55.175
- The age of the dinosaurs
is over.

02:56.915 --> 02:58.221
[door opens]

02:58.265 --> 02:59.657
- [sighing]
Whew! I'm beat.

02:59.701 --> 03:02.007
[chuckles] Hope your mama
didn't make the bed,

03:02.051 --> 03:03.922
'cause I'm just gonna
mess it up again.

03:03.966 --> 03:05.272
- Have you been out all night?

03:05.315 --> 03:07.230
- Mr. 20 Questions over here.

03:07.274 --> 03:09.537
Yes, I was out
with the guys.

03:11.539 --> 03:13.193
- My mom was
killing herself working

03:13.236 --> 03:14.759
and he was out all night?

03:14.803 --> 03:16.326
- That must have been
upsetting.

03:16.370 --> 03:18.023
- I was pissed, man...

03:18.067 --> 03:19.547
[suspenseful funky music]

03:19.590 --> 03:22.332
So when I found out later
he was going out again,

03:22.376 --> 03:25.857
I followed him so I could
give him a piece of my mind.

03:25.901 --> 03:27.119
Chi-Chi's?

03:27.163 --> 03:28.338
I'm eating baby hash browns

03:28.382 --> 03:29.905
and he's ordering
all-you-can-eat fajitas?

03:29.948 --> 03:31.254
Hell no.

03:31.298 --> 03:33.387
- Chi-Chi's?
That Tex-Mex chain?

03:33.430 --> 03:37.347
- Oh, yeah. Best and only
chimichangas in Pennsylvania.

03:37.391 --> 03:40.089
[light music playing over PA]

03:40.132 --> 03:46.530
♪

03:46.574 --> 03:49.533
Yo, Dad.
Enjoying some chimichangas?

03:49.577 --> 03:52.057
- Dewey.
What are you doing here?

03:52.101 --> 03:53.363
- I followed you.

03:53.407 --> 03:54.712
- You followed me?

03:54.756 --> 03:57.149
Son, what I do
is none of your damn business.

03:57.193 --> 03:58.368
- I'm making it my business.

03:58.412 --> 03:59.891
You're staying out all night

03:59.935 --> 04:01.676
then treating yourself
to some hangover nachos

04:01.719 --> 04:03.373
while Mom is working all day.

04:03.417 --> 04:05.245
- Fine, fine!

04:05.288 --> 04:08.987
You wanna know what's going on,
I'll tell you what's going on.

04:09.031 --> 04:11.294
It all started the other day
at this gas station.

04:11.338 --> 04:14.645
[upbeat music]

04:14.689 --> 04:16.256
- Hey.

04:16.299 --> 04:18.475
Hey! Hey, you Rocky Johnson?

04:18.519 --> 04:21.696
- The one and only.
- [laughs] Oh, man.

04:21.739 --> 04:23.654
I thought that was you,
Soulman.

04:23.698 --> 04:27.179
Look, I used to watch you
wrestle on TV all the time.

04:27.223 --> 04:28.485
Oh, man. You were the best.

04:28.529 --> 04:29.921
- Still am the best.

04:29.965 --> 04:32.576
- Oh, that's right, Soulman.
That's right. [laughs]

04:32.620 --> 04:33.751
Hey, hey, can I get
your autograph?

04:33.795 --> 04:35.275
Look, my wife is gonna
go nuts

04:35.318 --> 04:36.276
when I tell her I met you.

04:36.319 --> 04:38.626
- Anything for a fan.

04:38.669 --> 04:42.238
- [laughs] Uh, make that out
to Gennifer with a G.

04:42.282 --> 04:44.327
- Hmm. You don't come across
that spelling too often.

04:44.371 --> 04:45.415
- Yeah.
[laughs]

04:45.459 --> 04:46.590
- Dad,
where is this story going?

04:46.634 --> 04:48.331
- I'm gettin' there.

04:48.375 --> 04:51.334
- So um, what you
been up to these days?

04:51.378 --> 04:53.815
- Oh, pfft, brother,
I am here and there.

04:53.858 --> 04:55.991
[laughs] You know,
this and that, just hustlin'.

04:56.034 --> 04:59.951
- Okay, all right.
Hey, you wanna make $500?

04:59.995 --> 05:01.910
- Oh, whoa, whoa, brother.
I ain't that kinda hustler.

05:01.953 --> 05:05.392
- Oh, no. [laughs]
No, no, no.

05:05.435 --> 05:06.654
What I'm sayin' is

05:06.697 --> 05:09.091
I got a job for you,
if you want one.

05:09.134 --> 05:10.353
You ever been to Chi-Chi's?

05:10.397 --> 05:12.355
- 'Course I have.
Love Chi-Chi's.

05:12.399 --> 05:14.052
[both laugh]

05:14.096 --> 05:15.402
Remind me what that is again.

05:15.445 --> 05:17.708
- Tex-Mex joint down
at the Lehigh Valley Mall.

05:17.752 --> 05:20.102
Go by there tomorrow evening,
talk to the manager.

05:20.145 --> 05:21.886
Tell him Don sent you, huh?

05:21.930 --> 05:22.670
- Don sent you?

05:22.713 --> 05:24.541
That piece of [bleep]

05:24.585 --> 05:26.456
hasn't shown up to work
in three weeks,

05:26.500 --> 05:27.457
and now he's
sending people over

05:27.501 --> 05:29.024
like he's doing me a favor?

05:29.067 --> 05:31.940
Where is he? Because I am gonna
run him over with my car!

05:31.983 --> 05:33.376
- Hey, hey.

05:33.420 --> 05:35.596
Let's take a breather.

05:35.639 --> 05:38.163
- [exhales deeply]
I'm sorry.

05:38.207 --> 05:39.339
I anger quickly.

05:39.382 --> 05:41.863
It's in my blood
from my mama's side.

05:43.038 --> 05:44.561
- Sure.

05:44.605 --> 05:47.259
But, hey, forget about Don.

05:47.303 --> 05:48.870
You got Rocky Johnson here.

05:48.913 --> 05:50.698
So whatever you hired Don
to do,

05:50.741 --> 05:52.003
I can do.

05:52.047 --> 05:54.745
- Do you know how
to deep clean a restaurant?

05:54.789 --> 05:56.834
- Of course I didn't know.
I ain't know a damn thing.

05:56.878 --> 05:58.880
[sucks teeth]
Of course I do.

05:58.923 --> 06:00.490
- [sighs]

06:00.534 --> 06:02.187
All right.

06:02.231 --> 06:04.581
Well, Don has left me
in a bind here, so...

06:04.625 --> 06:06.061
I'm gonna give you a shot.

06:06.104 --> 06:08.977
- [sighs and chuckles]
That's great.

06:09.020 --> 06:11.153
Pays 500 bucks?
- Yeah, a week, yeah.

06:11.196 --> 06:12.850
If you do a good job.

06:12.894 --> 06:15.113
Now, it also takes all night.

06:15.157 --> 06:16.767
Okay, so I'm gonna have to
lock you inside the building

06:16.811 --> 06:18.943
until morning
so you can't steal anything.

06:18.987 --> 06:20.902
- What would I steal
from Chi-Chi's?

06:20.945 --> 06:22.860
- We have some
fine artwork here.

06:25.428 --> 06:26.864
- Uh--wait, wait, wait.
[chuckles]

06:26.908 --> 06:28.039
Is it even legal

06:28.083 --> 06:30.390
to lock someone
in a building like this?

06:30.433 --> 06:31.695
- See you in the morning!

06:31.739 --> 06:32.783
[suspenseful funky music]

06:32.827 --> 06:34.568
- Uh--
[lock clanks]

06:34.611 --> 06:36.308
♪

06:36.352 --> 06:38.702
So I stayed and cleaned
through the night,

06:38.746 --> 06:40.791
which is why I came home
looking all ragged.

06:40.835 --> 06:43.446
- Hey, hey, hey.
Who's this?

06:43.490 --> 06:45.709
- This is my son.
Got an extra set of hands.

06:45.753 --> 06:47.885
- Okay, well,
see you in the morning.

06:47.929 --> 06:50.932
- All right.
Have a good night.

06:50.975 --> 06:52.237
[lock clanks]

06:52.281 --> 06:53.674
- I don't know what your face
looks like

06:53.717 --> 06:55.066
when you're locked
in a Chi-Chi's all night,

06:55.110 --> 06:56.198
but that's what mine
looked like.

06:58.418 --> 06:58.548
.

06:58.592 --> 07:00.507
[buttons clacking]
- One, two,

07:00.550 --> 07:02.204
three!
- Oh! My joystick got stuck.

07:02.247 --> 07:03.553
- [mocking]
Oh, my joystick got stuck.

07:03.597 --> 07:05.555
Come on, losers have been
saying that since '77.

07:05.599 --> 07:07.557
- Ah, I shouldn't have
lotioned my hands.

07:07.601 --> 07:09.037
- Should I get back
to the story?

07:09.080 --> 07:10.995
- Oh, uh, right,
so, uh,

07:11.039 --> 07:12.823
you're locked in a Chi-Chi's
with your dad.

07:12.867 --> 07:15.565
- Yes,
and I am not happy about it.

07:15.609 --> 07:16.914
[door rattling]

07:16.958 --> 07:19.221
[sighs]

07:19.264 --> 07:21.745
I can't believe
he actually locked us in.

07:21.789 --> 07:25.227
- You got to earn the keys
to Chi-Chi's. [chuckles]

07:25.270 --> 07:26.837
I earned 'em day one.

07:26.881 --> 07:28.796
Then lost 'em that afternoon.

07:28.839 --> 07:30.406
Literally in a rain gutter.

07:30.450 --> 07:32.060
Now I gotta earn 'em again.
- Great.

07:32.103 --> 07:34.062
Now I'm locked in here
all night.

07:34.105 --> 07:36.630
- What's with you?
Why you so angry?

07:36.673 --> 07:38.414
All I'm trying to do
is help pay the bills.

07:38.458 --> 07:39.502
- I'm not gonna
give you a medal

07:39.546 --> 07:40.851
for doing what
you're supposed to do.

07:40.895 --> 07:42.418
And why'd you lie about
being out with the guys?

07:42.462 --> 07:44.376
Were you embarrassed
about working here?

07:44.420 --> 07:46.944
- No. It would just take
too much to convey.

07:46.988 --> 07:48.598
You heard my long-ass
explanation.

07:48.642 --> 07:50.034
- Come on, Dad.

07:50.078 --> 07:51.514
You could've easily
shaved five minutes off that.

07:51.558 --> 07:53.385
- Don't tell a storyteller
how to tell a story.

07:53.429 --> 07:55.953
People love long stories.
You should remember that.

07:55.997 --> 07:57.259
[laughs]

07:57.302 --> 07:58.913
[gasps]
[suspenseful music]

07:58.956 --> 08:00.262
Oh, no.

08:00.305 --> 08:02.438
Oh, my claustrophobia
is setting in.

08:02.482 --> 08:03.744
Son, come on.
Help me to the bar.

08:03.787 --> 08:05.267
I need a drink.

08:05.310 --> 08:07.095
- Wait, how could your dad
be claustrophobic

08:07.138 --> 08:08.444
in a large space like that?

08:08.488 --> 08:10.533
- He was genuinely
claustrophobic,

08:10.577 --> 08:12.840
and it would flare up
at odd times.

08:12.883 --> 08:14.058
But I shared your skepticism.

08:14.102 --> 08:16.104
Dad, this place is literally

08:16.147 --> 08:18.149
three times the size
of our apartment.

08:18.193 --> 08:19.542
- Hey, Dwayne,

08:19.586 --> 08:21.544
everything's three times
the size of our apartment.

08:21.588 --> 08:23.111
[can hisses and snaps]
[Rocky sighs]

08:25.809 --> 08:27.158
[sighs]
That's better.

08:27.202 --> 08:29.509
- Guess that's coming off
the paycheck.

08:29.552 --> 08:33.382
- Listen, I don't have
any more time for your guff.

08:33.425 --> 08:35.776
- My guff?
[Rocky sighs]

08:35.819 --> 08:37.429
We got work to do.

08:37.473 --> 08:39.910
You sweep in here.
I'll mop the kitchen.

08:39.954 --> 08:41.651
[Dwayne sighs]

08:43.174 --> 08:46.743
- So I got to work...

08:46.787 --> 08:49.050
until I realized...

08:49.093 --> 08:50.747
What the hell am I doing?

08:50.791 --> 08:53.097
[broom clatters]

08:53.141 --> 08:55.404
[arcade game music playing]

08:55.447 --> 08:57.493
- Already taking a break, huh?

08:57.537 --> 08:59.626
You better be playing
as your old man.

08:59.669 --> 09:02.454
- I'm sorry to say you are not
a character in "WrestleFest."

09:02.498 --> 09:04.108
- Yes, I am.
A secret character!

09:04.152 --> 09:05.370
You gotta unlock me.

09:05.414 --> 09:08.591
And you can play me
in jeans or trunks.

09:08.635 --> 09:09.636
- Dad, come on.

09:09.679 --> 09:10.854
- I'm serious.

09:10.898 --> 09:12.943
- Why are you always
working the gimmick?

09:12.987 --> 09:14.336
- [laughs]
What you talkin' 'bout?

09:14.379 --> 09:16.556
I'm not always
working the gimmick.

09:16.599 --> 09:18.209
Ah, that's my boy.
- [laughs]

09:18.253 --> 09:20.429
- Hey, and after, I promise
we'll get some ice cream.

09:20.472 --> 09:21.256
- Okay.

09:21.299 --> 09:22.605
- And when I get back,

09:22.649 --> 09:24.433
I'm gonna get us a place
before she even gets here.

09:24.476 --> 09:25.695
Don't worry about that.

09:25.739 --> 09:27.523
- Do you know how
to deep clean a restaurant?

09:27.567 --> 09:28.698
- Of course I do.

09:28.742 --> 09:30.265
Okay, enough. I get it.

09:30.308 --> 09:31.832
But I swear
there is a cheat code.

09:31.875 --> 09:33.964
Here. Move, move, move.

09:34.008 --> 09:36.488
All right, it's, uh,
up, up--no.

09:36.532 --> 09:39.622
Up, down, left, right,
punch, punch--

09:39.666 --> 09:42.277
where's the start button?
Uh--

09:42.320 --> 09:44.671
- Dad, can you please
just be honest?

09:44.714 --> 09:46.629
- [scoffing chuckle]
What kind of question is that?

09:46.673 --> 09:48.457
- You're like
that wooden puppet boy.

09:48.500 --> 09:49.850
You know, what's his name.

09:49.893 --> 09:51.199
- Pinochilo.

09:51.242 --> 09:53.157
- It is definitely not
Pinochilo.

09:53.201 --> 09:54.811
- All right,
you want some honesty?

09:54.855 --> 09:56.117
I'll give you some honesty.

09:57.684 --> 10:00.295
Ask me anything.

10:00.338 --> 10:02.123
- Your dad really said
you could ask him anything?

10:02.166 --> 10:03.733
Nothing off-limits?
- Nothing.

10:03.777 --> 10:05.692
But I wasn't sure
if I could trust him,

10:05.735 --> 10:08.042
so I set a little trap
and I asked him a question

10:08.085 --> 10:10.261
that I already
knew the answer to.

10:10.305 --> 10:13.656
What caused your career to end
in the WWF?

10:13.700 --> 10:14.875
- [inhales deeply]

10:14.918 --> 10:16.920
Vince let me go
because I almost agreed

10:16.964 --> 10:19.575
to wrestle with another
promoter in Saudi Arabia,

10:19.619 --> 10:21.925
even though I was excusive
with the WWF.

10:21.969 --> 10:24.972
And let's face it: my run
was just coming to an end.

10:25.929 --> 10:27.975
But you already knew that,
didn't you?

10:28.018 --> 10:31.195
- Yeah. Bam Bam Bigelow
told me back in Nashville.

10:31.239 --> 10:33.110
- And that's the last time
I trust a man

10:33.154 --> 10:34.590
with a flame tattoo
on his head.

10:34.634 --> 10:37.071
But, hey, I told the truth.
You happy?

10:37.114 --> 10:39.377
- I'm more surprised you didn't
take an hour to explain it.

10:39.421 --> 10:42.119
- Oh, I can give you
that version, too, Son.

10:42.163 --> 10:44.295
- Dad, it's okay.
I got the gist.

10:44.339 --> 10:46.733
- Well, all right, then.
We got a restaurant to clean.

10:46.776 --> 10:47.864
- [sighs softly]

10:47.908 --> 10:49.605
- And if you help me...

10:49.649 --> 10:51.999
I'll answer any question
you got.

10:52.042 --> 10:53.522
Honestly.

10:53.565 --> 10:54.915
Deal?

10:54.958 --> 10:56.307
- Game on.

10:58.353 --> 10:58.745
.

10:58.788 --> 11:01.095
- So all those times
you swore off drinking,

11:01.138 --> 11:02.836
did you ever actually quit?
- Sure did.

11:02.879 --> 11:04.664
Back in '86,
I quit for a few months.

11:04.707 --> 11:06.753
[chuckles] Weeks.

11:08.319 --> 11:09.669
Three days?

11:09.712 --> 11:11.279
- When I was in second grade,

11:11.322 --> 11:12.541
you said you couldn't help me
with my solar system diorama

11:12.584 --> 11:14.151
because of arthritis.

11:14.195 --> 11:15.500
Was that true?

11:15.544 --> 11:16.763
- Nope.

11:16.806 --> 11:19.069
I just don't believe
in Jupiter's rings, Son.

11:19.113 --> 11:21.419
And I didn't wanna get
into that with a kid.

11:21.463 --> 11:22.899
[toilet flushes]

11:22.943 --> 11:24.771
- Have you ever
stolen anything?

11:24.814 --> 11:26.729
- Besides
a few girl's hearts?

11:26.773 --> 11:28.252
[chuckles]

11:28.296 --> 11:29.906
Yes. Yes, I have.

11:29.950 --> 11:31.429
I remember
the first time I stole.

11:31.473 --> 11:34.258
It was a bottle of Tums
that I stuffed down my pants.

11:34.302 --> 11:36.565
But I got caught
by the store employee.

11:36.608 --> 11:38.698
Damn things made
too much noise.

11:38.741 --> 11:39.960
- Who steals Tums?

11:40.003 --> 11:42.136
- I was six, Son.
I thought they was candy.

11:42.179 --> 11:44.834
- My dad was finally
opening up, so I did, too.

11:44.878 --> 11:46.444
- Hiding the goods
in your pants.

11:46.488 --> 11:47.663
That's amateur hour, Dad.

11:47.707 --> 11:48.925
- Eh, what do you know?

11:48.969 --> 11:51.319
- I know shoplifters
are always trying to hide

11:51.362 --> 11:54.452
what they're stealing, which
makes 'em seem more suspicious.

11:54.496 --> 11:57.064
- When I steal stuff, I just
act like I already own it.

11:57.107 --> 11:58.413
- You steal?

11:58.456 --> 12:00.023
- How do you think I got
all those nice clothes?

12:00.067 --> 12:01.982
- I don't know. I don't think
about your clothes.

12:02.025 --> 12:03.897
But that being said,
you're grounded for a week.

12:03.940 --> 12:06.638
- [laughs] Mom already
punished me for that.

12:06.682 --> 12:08.292
Took all my nice clothes
to Goodwill.

12:08.336 --> 12:09.641
- Mom did?

12:09.685 --> 12:11.078
Oh, she didn't even tell me.

12:11.121 --> 12:12.775
Look at her protecting you.

12:12.819 --> 12:14.298
Ooh, speaking of your mom,

12:14.342 --> 12:16.300
you know her favorite earrings
she's always wearing?

12:16.344 --> 12:17.475
- The corn ones.

12:17.519 --> 12:19.521
- What woman's gonna wear
corn earrings?

12:19.564 --> 12:20.957
Those are pineapples, Son.

12:21.001 --> 12:23.960
Anyway, I lifted those
from Montgomery Ward's.

12:24.004 --> 12:26.136
Shoved 'em down my pants.
- What?

12:26.180 --> 12:28.182
Wait, and Mom knows this?
- Oh, hell no.

12:28.225 --> 12:30.358
This was early
in our relationship.

12:30.401 --> 12:32.142
Boy, I really wanted
to impress her.

12:32.186 --> 12:34.188
- I guess it worked.
- You bet your ass, it did.

12:34.231 --> 12:35.450
[both laugh]

12:37.931 --> 12:39.976
- So do you really work
the whole time you're here?

12:41.717 --> 12:44.111
- Chimichangas up!
[laughs]

12:44.154 --> 12:45.982
- Guess that's coming out
of your paycheck, too.

12:46.026 --> 12:48.289
- No. Manager said I could eat
whatever I want

12:48.332 --> 12:49.246
while I'm working.

12:51.509 --> 12:53.033
- [blowing]

12:54.512 --> 12:56.732
Oh, wow!

12:56.776 --> 12:57.820
That's really good!

12:57.864 --> 12:59.169
Hey, you should try
fried ice cream.

12:59.213 --> 13:00.736
[upbeat percussive music]

13:00.780 --> 13:01.824
- You can fry ice cream?

13:01.868 --> 13:04.653
- You can deep fry anything,
Son.

13:04.696 --> 13:06.698
Watch this.

13:06.742 --> 13:08.265
How about some fried salad?
- Mm-hmm.

13:08.309 --> 13:09.310
- [chuckles]

13:09.353 --> 13:10.833
♪

13:10.877 --> 13:12.487
[oil bubbling loudly]

13:12.530 --> 13:14.402
Oh, ooh!
The oil's angry!

13:14.445 --> 13:15.577
- Ah! It burns!

13:15.620 --> 13:16.883
- Add more stuff!
That'll calm it down!

13:16.926 --> 13:19.842
♪

13:19.886 --> 13:21.670
[laughter]

13:21.713 --> 13:23.846
[crunching]

13:23.890 --> 13:25.500
- Mm.

13:25.543 --> 13:27.502
This is definitely proof that
you can't deep fry everything.

13:27.545 --> 13:29.373
- It tastes delicious to me.

13:29.417 --> 13:33.029
That fried coating adds a nice
pork flavor to the lettuce.

13:33.073 --> 13:34.596
I told the manager about it
last week.

13:34.639 --> 13:35.771
He putting it on the menu.

13:35.815 --> 13:37.729
- See, there you go again
with the lies.

13:37.773 --> 13:39.253
- Oh, take it easy.

13:39.296 --> 13:40.863
I'm not lying.
It's just spin.

13:40.907 --> 13:42.822
- Here we go.
- Listen.

13:42.865 --> 13:44.475
There are various degrees
of lying,

13:44.519 --> 13:46.477
and they should not
be treated the same.

13:46.521 --> 13:49.045
Haven't you ever heard
of the lie pyramid?

13:49.089 --> 13:50.655
At the bottom, there's spin.

13:50.699 --> 13:52.179
That's just like
working a gimmick.

13:52.222 --> 13:53.920
Then, we have a white lie,

13:53.963 --> 13:56.444
inconsequential lie,
lie of omission,

13:56.487 --> 13:58.663
and at the tippy top
of that bad boy

13:58.707 --> 13:59.882
is a bald-faced lie.
- [scoffs]

13:59.926 --> 14:02.145
- Me, I'm mostly spinning.

14:02.189 --> 14:03.973
- Seems like you've put
a lot of thought into this.

14:04.017 --> 14:05.757
- Eh, lotta downtime
on the road.

14:05.801 --> 14:07.237
[laughs]

14:07.281 --> 14:10.110
But hey, sometimes a lie
makes life a little easier.

14:10.153 --> 14:12.982
- Yeah, for you.
- No, everybody.

14:13.026 --> 14:15.071
Remember your ex-girlfriend
Karen?

14:15.115 --> 14:17.421
You told me
you broke up with her.

14:17.465 --> 14:19.206
But you didn't, did you?

14:19.249 --> 14:22.078
- Yeah, she dumped me.
- Ah, see?

14:22.122 --> 14:23.688
But it was easier
to tell people

14:23.732 --> 14:24.994
it was the other way around.

14:25.038 --> 14:26.866
- Okay.
Maybe you have a point.

14:26.909 --> 14:28.389
- Mm.

14:28.432 --> 14:30.478
- But how'd you know
I lied about that?

14:30.521 --> 14:33.481
- I'm an emotionally
intelligent person.

14:33.524 --> 14:35.135
Also, Karen was
way outta your league,

14:35.178 --> 14:36.571
and that's the truth.

14:36.614 --> 14:38.312
[both laugh]

14:38.355 --> 14:39.400
[upbeat music]

14:39.443 --> 14:40.923
- I'm just sayin',
sparkling water

14:40.967 --> 14:43.795
should cost less
because it's half air.

14:43.839 --> 14:45.319
- I like your thinking, Son.

14:45.362 --> 14:47.364
♪

14:47.408 --> 14:50.106
Hey, now let me ask you
a question.

14:50.150 --> 14:51.281
- Shoot.

14:51.325 --> 14:54.502
- When'd you stop
looking up to your pops?

14:54.545 --> 14:55.764
- What?

14:55.807 --> 14:57.157
- You used to be
my biggest fan.

14:57.200 --> 14:59.115
- I'm still your biggest fan.
- Eh.

14:59.159 --> 15:02.031
We both know it's not the same.

15:02.075 --> 15:05.121
Was it when I started
wrestling in flea markets?

15:05.165 --> 15:06.949
Hey, we're being honest
tonight, right?

15:06.993 --> 15:09.256
- I have always loved
watching you wrestle.

15:09.299 --> 15:10.300
Still do.

15:10.344 --> 15:11.911
Doesn't matter where
or for who.

15:13.260 --> 15:14.870
- Oh, no.

15:14.914 --> 15:17.960
It's because you saw me cry
when we watched "The Fly."

15:18.004 --> 15:19.614
- That was surprising.

15:19.657 --> 15:22.312
- That poor baboon
got turned inside out.

15:22.356 --> 15:24.706
- Look, it wasn't just
one thing, okay?

15:24.749 --> 15:26.403
It was a slow build over time.

15:27.622 --> 15:29.798
- Come on, Son.

15:29.841 --> 15:31.104
When did it start?

15:31.147 --> 15:33.367
- All right.
Want the truth?

15:33.410 --> 15:34.542
- Yeah.

15:34.585 --> 15:35.935
- I don't know.

15:35.978 --> 15:37.980
I guess when I realized
that you weren't, like,

15:38.024 --> 15:39.373
the superhero.

15:39.416 --> 15:42.419
You're just a guy.

15:42.463 --> 15:46.075
- Just a guy
cleaning a restaurant, huh?

15:46.119 --> 15:47.729
You're embarrassed by that?

15:47.772 --> 15:48.991
- I'm not saying that, but--

15:49.035 --> 15:50.384
- But what?

15:52.603 --> 15:54.127
[scoffs]

16:00.524 --> 16:00.742
.

16:00.785 --> 16:02.874
[somber music]

16:02.918 --> 16:06.269
♪

16:06.313 --> 16:07.836
- You just gonna
ignore me all night?

16:07.879 --> 16:14.799
♪

16:16.584 --> 16:19.891
I know you're upset,
but how am I supposed to feel?

16:19.935 --> 16:21.458
We can barely make rent,
and I'm eating

16:21.502 --> 16:24.026
discount dinosaur hash browns
for breakfast.

16:24.070 --> 16:27.116
♪

16:27.160 --> 16:29.379
Look, at the end of the day,

16:29.423 --> 16:32.295
I know you're trying
to make things better.

16:32.339 --> 16:35.820
I appreciate you doing
what you can do to support us,

16:35.864 --> 16:39.172
including this job
at Chi-Chi's.

16:39.215 --> 16:41.565
- You don't have
to spin this, Son.

16:41.609 --> 16:43.524
- I'm not spinning.
- Yes, you are.

16:43.567 --> 16:45.656
You're spinning it
to make me feel better.

16:45.700 --> 16:46.962
- What do you mean?

16:47.006 --> 16:49.834
- I've made more than
a few mistakes, Dewey.

16:49.878 --> 16:53.795
What happened in Saudi Arabia,
Nashville.

16:53.838 --> 16:57.146
I put our family
in this position.

16:57.190 --> 16:58.974
I looked out for myself

16:59.018 --> 17:01.063
and hurt the people
I was supposed to protect.

17:01.107 --> 17:04.806
♪

17:04.849 --> 17:05.981
- So was this the first time

17:06.025 --> 17:07.722
your dad was real with you
like that?

17:07.765 --> 17:09.941
- Honestly,
I think this was the first time

17:09.985 --> 17:12.074
he had been truly real
with himself.

17:12.118 --> 17:13.858
[buttons clicking]

17:13.902 --> 17:17.514
I waited 16 years
to have a moment like that.

17:17.558 --> 17:20.735
And that really
meant something to me.

17:20.778 --> 17:22.650
It meant that
maybe I could trust him.

17:22.693 --> 17:25.522
- Mm. Good for Rocky.

17:25.566 --> 17:27.872
- Eh. It only lasted a second.

17:27.916 --> 17:29.396
[laughs]

17:29.831 --> 17:31.963
- You gonna say something or
just look at me all bug-eyed?

17:32.007 --> 17:34.966
- No.
I think you said it all.

17:35.010 --> 17:36.011
- Good.

17:36.055 --> 17:37.404
And, hey...

17:37.447 --> 17:39.058
you're welcome.
- For what?

17:39.101 --> 17:41.582
- If I didn't create
these challenges for you,

17:41.625 --> 17:43.410
you wouldn't have that huge
chip on your shoulder.

17:43.453 --> 17:44.759
- How is that a good thing?

17:44.802 --> 17:47.414
- It pushed you to work
your ass off, didn't it?

17:47.457 --> 17:49.242
And now you're going
to Miami, baby,

17:49.285 --> 17:51.157
so yeah, you're welcome.

17:51.200 --> 17:52.723
- Are you seriously trying
to take credit

17:52.767 --> 17:54.203
for me playing football
for the Canes?

17:54.247 --> 17:55.813
- Hell yeah, I am.

17:58.512 --> 18:02.516
[both laugh]

18:02.559 --> 18:04.213
- I thought we weren't
spinning anymore.

18:04.257 --> 18:06.259
- I know, I know.

18:06.302 --> 18:07.738
[buttons clicking]

18:07.782 --> 18:09.958
You gotta admit, this game
would be a lot better

18:10.001 --> 18:11.307
if I was in it.
- [scoffs]

18:11.351 --> 18:12.743
You say that about every game.

18:12.787 --> 18:14.136
You even said that about chess.

18:14.180 --> 18:16.269
- Why shouldn't Rocky Johnson
be a knight?

18:16.312 --> 18:17.879
[chuckles]

18:18.880 --> 18:20.577
Oh, shoot.
The boss is here!

18:20.621 --> 18:22.144
Quick, get the ice cream!

18:22.188 --> 18:23.537
- You said we could eat
whatever we want,

18:23.580 --> 18:24.581
as long as it--

18:24.625 --> 18:25.756
that was a lie, wasn't it?

18:25.800 --> 18:27.193
- Of course it was a lie!

18:27.236 --> 18:28.759
You think Chi-Chi's is just
giving away free food?

18:28.803 --> 18:31.588
Come on! I thought
you was going to college.

18:31.632 --> 18:34.809
- Okay, everything looks good.

18:34.852 --> 18:36.941
My beautiful paintings
are still here.

18:36.985 --> 18:39.030
You did a good job, guys.
- Thank you.

18:39.074 --> 18:40.771
- Make sure to let me know
you got the paycheck, okay?

18:40.815 --> 18:42.251
I put it in the mail.
- Appreciate that.

18:42.295 --> 18:43.600
Come on, Dewey. Let's go.

18:43.644 --> 18:44.775
- You know, you shouldn't be
locking people

18:44.819 --> 18:47.430
in this restaurant.
- I said let's go.

18:47.474 --> 18:48.953
- That painting is ugly.

18:51.608 --> 18:53.088
- Kid's nuts.

18:55.046 --> 18:57.962
- Hey, babe. Before Dad tries
to spin anything,

18:58.006 --> 18:59.616
we were at Chi-Chi's
all night cleaning.

18:59.660 --> 19:00.878
- She knows that, Son.

19:00.922 --> 19:02.271
- I don't know what you said.

19:02.315 --> 19:04.273
- We got your first paycheck
from Chi-chi's,

19:04.317 --> 19:05.448
but I think something's wrong.

19:05.492 --> 19:06.971
- Oh, this can't be right.

19:07.015 --> 19:09.322
- Don't tell me they took out
the drinks and the food.

19:09.365 --> 19:12.890
- This is a check for $8,000.

19:14.283 --> 19:15.676
[dial tone buzzing]

19:15.719 --> 19:17.243
- Dad, what are you doing?
[dialing tones chiming]

19:17.286 --> 19:18.505
- Don't tell the manager.
He's gonna take the money back.

19:18.548 --> 19:21.508
- Hey, I did honest work.
I want honest pay.

19:21.551 --> 19:24.119
[line trilling]
Hey, it's Rocky Johnson.

19:24.163 --> 19:25.207
I got my check,

19:25.251 --> 19:26.774
and I think
you have a sticky zero

19:26.817 --> 19:28.079
on your keyboard over there.

19:28.123 --> 19:30.560
- Yeah, well, I included
all of Don's backpay.

19:30.604 --> 19:31.866
That piece of [bleep]
never showed up

19:31.909 --> 19:33.084
to pick up his checks,

19:33.128 --> 19:35.739
so I am happy
you're getting his money.

19:35.783 --> 19:38.264
- Oh, okay. Hey, I'm more
than happy to take it.

19:38.307 --> 19:40.527
Thank you.
- I'll bet you are. Enjoy.

19:41.223 --> 19:42.137
Carlos!

19:42.181 --> 19:44.313
- It's real!
It's our money!

19:44.357 --> 19:46.446
- Oh, my God!
[laughter]

19:46.489 --> 19:49.275
Oh, it's a miracle.
- Oh.

19:49.318 --> 19:51.799
Look who's taking care
of the family now!

19:51.842 --> 19:53.670
[laughs]
This is why you always

19:53.714 --> 19:55.106
talk to strangers
at gas stations.

19:55.150 --> 19:57.544
- That really happened?
- It did.

19:57.587 --> 20:00.503
And that money
really saved us, man.

20:00.547 --> 20:01.983
Do you know, in a way,
that night

20:02.026 --> 20:04.551
that my dad and I spent
in Chi-Chi's,

20:04.594 --> 20:07.467
it might've saved us, too.
- Huh.

20:07.510 --> 20:09.686
That's an amazing story,
Dwayne.

20:09.730 --> 20:11.340
I can't believe your dad--ooh!

20:11.384 --> 20:12.907
I just pinned your ass!

20:12.950 --> 20:14.691
- Come on!
- Yes, yes, yes!

20:14.735 --> 20:16.693
I did it!
Me and Mr. Perfect did it.

20:16.737 --> 20:18.260
- I was trying to tell a story.

20:18.304 --> 20:19.827
- And it was a great one.

20:19.870 --> 20:22.003
- [laughs]
Hey, Prime Minister.

20:22.046 --> 20:24.005
- I am so sorry to listen in,

20:24.048 --> 20:25.398
but I just didn't want
to interrupt.

20:25.441 --> 20:27.356
- Not at all. It's a real
pleasure to meet you.

20:27.400 --> 20:29.358
- Oh, it is a pleasure
to meet you, as well.

20:29.402 --> 20:31.969
I really am a fan.
- It's an honor. Thank you.

20:32.013 --> 20:34.058
- You know, you can tell
the makeup of a person

20:34.102 --> 20:36.713
not only by how they handle
life's tough moments,

20:36.757 --> 20:39.412
but also how they handle
the victories.

20:39.455 --> 20:40.761
- Is that a line
from "Jumanji"?

20:40.804 --> 20:43.285
- Man, come on.
- No, I just said that now

20:43.329 --> 20:46.723
because you weren't
a very gracious winner.

20:46.767 --> 20:47.724
- Not very gracious.

20:47.768 --> 20:48.769
- Oh--
[stammers]

20:48.812 --> 20:50.292
Well, he was beating me
all day.

20:50.336 --> 20:51.685
- [scoffs]

20:51.728 --> 20:52.729
- Prime Minister, we were just
admiring the room.

20:52.773 --> 20:54.905
It's very impressive.
- Thank you.

20:54.949 --> 20:56.559
And I am looking forward
to talking with you

20:56.603 --> 20:59.562
about that and so much more
at tonight's welcome dinner.

20:59.606 --> 21:00.998
- Can't wait.
- Okay.

21:01.042 --> 21:03.871
I had them place my name
placard right next to yours.

21:03.914 --> 21:06.352
- Hey, side by side.
[laughter]

21:06.395 --> 21:07.788
- Um, do I get a placard?

21:07.831 --> 21:09.268
- I have no idea.

21:10.356 --> 21:12.575
If you like,
I can request our chefs

21:12.619 --> 21:14.229
to make you
some fried ice cream

21:14.273 --> 21:15.883
just like at Chi-Chi's.
- Wow!

21:15.926 --> 21:18.146
- Oh. What ever happened
to Chi-Chi's?

21:18.189 --> 21:19.713
That chain used to be
so popular.

21:19.756 --> 21:21.105
- Yeah.
- Oh.

21:21.149 --> 21:22.716
- You know, I don't know.
- Hmm.

21:22.759 --> 21:25.675
[somber mandolin music]

21:25.719 --> 21:29.505
♪

21:29.549 --> 21:30.637
- I think that's a good idea.
